<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-23T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-23T23:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.77/1493</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-24T12:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1915,
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Managing director of Hukuang Railway agrees to accept tenders for ten
                            locomotives with alternative American standard specifications. Copies of
                            the tenders to be opened on January 15 in New York have been sent to
                            Hunt.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>